WorldStage Newsonline– The Chief of the Air Staff (CAS), Air Vice Marshal Oladayo Amao, has ordered an immediate investigation into the crash of a Nigerian Air Force (NAF) Beechcraft KingAir B350i aircraft while returning to the Abuja Airport after reporting engine failure enroute Minna. In the NAF official statement on the accident, CAS  urged the general public to remain calm and await the outcome of investigation. The statement confirmed that all 7 personnel on board died in the crash. The CAS  on behalf of all NAF personnel, “commiserates with the families of the deceased.”